<div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent"><br />What's a Dendy?<br /></div><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Russia's unlicensed version of the Famicom. Apparently it has some unique hardware differences.<br /></div><br />Generally speaking, it's the Asian PAL-Famiclones based on the <a href="http://img94.imageshack.us/gal.php?g=originalfamicloneumc.jpg" class="postlink">6527P/6538</a> chips (Dendy, Microgenius, Pegasus, etc.)<br />Oscilloscope tests HERE:<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?t=5070">http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?t=5070</a><!-- m --><br />Vblank, NMI, scanlines, PPU etc.<br /><br />Can someone fix nestopia's "dendy-mode" according these tests?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3884">Eugene.S</a> — Wed Apr 07, 2010 2:12 am</p><hr />
