<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5702&amp;p=59621#p59621"><![CDATA[
I was confused when I read about your method.<br /><br />But if you want to measure a <em>lot</em> of frame timings to calibrate your engine, that's what a copyright notice screen is for.[1] You get at least 120 chances to measure frame timing while it is displayed. Besides, you can find the end of vertical blanking by waiting for the sprite 0 flag to turn off.<br /><br /><br /><span style="font-size: 84%; line-height: normal">[1] That and decompressing the title screen tiles.</span><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Sun Apr 04, 2010 4:51 pm</p><hr />
